INSTALLING
==========

Run "./install.sh [argument list]" where arguments are:

--server	install server part (core and node process)
--client	install object management library (Python)
--webadmin	install webadmin (wsgi script, static files and apache2 configuration)

CONFIGURING SERVER
==================

cd into "/opt/b2project" and copy "conf.sample" into "conf". Then edit configuration files within newly created directory according to your needs.

USING CLIENT LIBRARY
====================

Using python interpreter execute:

>>> import b2lib
>>> app = b2lib.Application()

then use any of its methods.

